<section class="guideSection">
  <h2>What Most People Get Wrong</h2>

  <p>
    <strong>They choose based on variety count.</strong> More seeds do not mean a better gift if many go unused.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>They prioritize novelty.</strong> Interesting crops often require more experience or space than expected.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>They ignore how the gardener actually grows.</strong> Space, climate, and preferences matter more than presentation.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="calloutBox">
  <h2>What Most People Should Actually Gift</h2>

  <p>
    For most situations, a balanced collection from Botanical Interests is the best choice because it combines usability with reliable performance. High Mowing is a strong alternative for organic-focused gardeners.
  </p>

  <p class="muted">
    The best collection is the one that gets planted.
  </p>
